# Frontend Change Governance Rules

## UI And Contract Compatibility

- Treat UI behavior and API consumption changes as compatibility-sensitive.
- Mark breaking UX or contract changes and provide transition notes.
- Keep changes incremental to reduce user-facing disruption.

## Dependency Governance

- Add frontend dependencies only when existing stack cannot solve the need.
- Evaluate bundle-size and maintenance impact before adoption.
- Document risk and rollback notes for major dependency changes.

## Configuration Discipline

- Keep environment-specific values in config/env, not hardcoded.
- Use safe defaults when runtime config is unavailable.
- Document feature flags and rollout strategy for risky behavior changes.
